## 6. Data Flow

```
User browses web
    ↓
content.js captures DOM events (click, input, scroll, navigation)
    ↓ chrome.runtime.sendMessage
background.js stores events in IndexedDB
    ↓ User clicks "Stop Recording"
background.js saves workflow → calls POST /api/describe
    ↓
FastAPI server → LLMClient (Gemini Pro) → returns {title, description, steps, required_inputs}
    ↓
background.js updates IndexedDB with AI analysis
    ↓ User clicks "Run" on dashboard
dashboard.js sends POST /api/automate with events + optional task_description + input_values
    ↓
server.py → task_manager.submit() → AutomationRunner.run_task()
    ↓
AutomationRunner creates Browser (Playwright Chromium) + Agent (browser-use + Gemini Flash)
    ↓
Agent executes task in real browser → returns result
    ↓
server.py returns {success, task_description, message, error} to extension
```

